You are free to:
- Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
- Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material

The licensor cannot revoke these freedoms as long as you follow the license terms.

Under the following terms:
- Attribution — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license, 
  and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable manner, but 
  not in any way that suggests the licensor endorses you or your use.
  
  *Example:* "This guide is based on [Git Tutorial](https://github.com/SynergOps/Git) by Sali Emin, available under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license."

- NonCommercial — You may not use the material for commercial purposes.

  *Allowed:* Use in free workshops, personal study, academic teaching.
  *NOT allowed:* Selling as a book, incorporating into commercial training platform, use in paid webinars.

- ShareAlike — If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you must 
  distribute your contributions under the same license as the original.
  
  *Example:* If you add new chapters or exercises, the new material must have the same CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license.

- No additional restrictions — You may not apply legal terms or technological 
  measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license permits.

NOTICES:
You do not have to comply with the license for elements of the material in the 
public domain or where your use is permitted by an applicable exception or limitation.

No warranties are given. The license may not give you all of the permissions 
necessary for your intended use. For example, other rights such as publicity, 
privacy, or moral rights may limit how you use the material.

